@JimmyXJames @CBSNews Hi Jimmy! This statistic came from a peer reviewed scientific study published in the Journal of Sex and Marital Therapy, published in 2017 titled “Prevalence of Experiences With Consensual Nonmonogamous Relationships”. Hope that helps!

@MechEngMan @CBSNews Hi there! This statistic came from a peer reviewed scientific study published in the Journal of Sex and Marital Therapy, published in 2017 titled “Prevalence of Experiences With Consensual Nonmonogamous Relationships”. Hope that helps!

@SpencerAveryR @CBSNews Hey Spencer! Polygamy is actually very different from polyamory. Polygamy is usually a religious/cultural practice where one man marries multiple women and is sometimes not a choice, while polyamory is romantic/sexual relationships between multiple consenting adults.
